pping \n**Goal:** Clip extreme HU values to the brain-relevant range [-100, 200] and normalize to [0, 1] for stable CNN training. This is applied BEFORE the windowing step in the full pipeline.\n\n**Problem Identified:** Raw HU values range from -1022 to +1647 in our test slice. CNNs cannot train effectively on such a wide range — extreme values distort gradients and slow down learning. We need to clip to a medically meaningful range and normalize to [0, 1].\n\n**Formula:**\n\n**Clipped**  = clip(HU, -100, 200)\n\n**Normalized =** (Clipped - (-100)) / (200 - (-100))\n           = (Clipped + 100) / 300\n\n           \n**Output range: [0.0, 1.0]**","metadata":{}},{"cell_type":"code","source":"# ── Assign negative case (already loaded in DICOM step) ───\nneg_hu = hu_image\nneg_id = slice_id\n\n# ── Load known positive SAH case ──────────────────────────\npositive_id = \"ID_aec8e68b3\"\npos_path    = os.path.join(TRAIN_DICOM_DIR, f\"{positive_id}.dcm\")\npos_dcm     = pydicom.dcmread(pos_path)\npos_raw     = pos_dcm.pixel_array.astype(np.float32)\npos_slope   = float(pos_dcm.RescaleSlope)     if hasattr(pos_dcm, 'RescaleSlope')     else 1.0\npos_inter   = float(pos_dcm.RescaleIntercept) if hasattr(pos_dcm, 'RescaleIntercept') else 0.0\npos_hu      = pos_raw * pos_slope + pos_inter\n\nprint(f\"✅ Negative slice : {neg_id}\")\nprint(f\"✅ Positive slice : {positive_id} (Subarachnoid Hemorrhage)\")\nprint(f\"\\n📋 HU Ranges:\")\nprint(f\"  Negative : [{neg_hu.min():.0f}, {neg_hu.max():.0f}]\")\nprint(f\"  Positive : [{pos_hu.min():.0f}, {pos_hu.max():.0f}]\")","metadata":{"trusted":true,"execution":{"iopub.status.busy":"2026-03-18T09:04:48.856362Z","iopub.execute_input":"2026-03-18T09:04:48.856677Z","iopub.status.idle":"2026-03-18T09:04:48.874597Z","shell.execute_reply.started":"2026-03-18T09:04:48.856650Z","shell.execute_reply":"2026-03-18T09:04:48.873893Z"}},"outputs":[{"name":"stdout","text":"✅ Negative slice : ID_27a354d42\n✅ Positive slice : ID_aec8e68b3 (Subarachnoid He